  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed House amended",
    "asOf": "2006-07-25",
    "date": "2006-09-06T17:50:12Z",
    "text": "(This measure has not been amended since it was reported to the House on July 17, 2006. The summary of that version is repeated here.)\n\nPromoting Transparency in Financial Reporting Act of 2006 - Requires the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), the Financial Accounting Standards Board, and the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board to provide oral testimony by their respective Chairpersons (or a designee), beginning in 2007, and annually for five years, to the Committee on Financial Services of the House of Representatives on their efforts to reduce the complexity in financial reporting to provide more accurate and clear financial information to investors."
  },
